The '''Togian golden bulbul''' ('''''Hypsipetes aureus''''') is a species of [[passerine]] bird in the bulbul family [[Pycnonotidae]]. It is [[Endemism|endemic]] to the [[Togian Islands]]  in Indonesia. Its natural [[habitat]] is subtropical or tropical moist lowland [[forest]]s.

The Togian golden bulbul was formerly considered as [[conspecific]] with   five other bulbuls, all called the [[northern golden bulbul]] before they were all split. This bulbul is now both placed with 24 other species in the genus ''[[Hypsipetes]]'' that was introduced in 1831 by [[Nicholas Aylward Vigors|Nicholas Vigors]].<ref name=ioc>{{cite web| editor1-last=Gill | editor1-first=Frank | editor1-link=Frank Gill (ornithologist) | editor2-last=Donsker | editor2-first=David | editor3-last=Rasmussen | editor3-first=Pamela | editor3-link=Pamela Rasmussen | date=July 2023 | title=Bulbuls | work=IOC World Bird List Version 13.2 | url=https://www.worldbirdnames.org/bow/bulbuls/ | publisher=International Ornithologists' Union | access-date=24 July 2023}}</ref>

